<span id="freeTextContainer2302344253179369366">In Hmong culture they revere their children so much, it is wonderful. This little girl was her parent&apos;s favorite and they believed her epilepsy was a special gift that made her more in tune with the spirit world. Many of the spirit healers in Hmong society have epilepsy.<br/>More largely, this is the story of a clash between western and eastern cultures, a communication lapse that ultimately ended up hurting the parents of this little girl very profoundly. </span>
